What date is Halloween celebrated every year?
Answer: October 31

Which ancient festival is considered the origin of Halloween?
Answer: Samhain

According to folklore, what animal is often a witch’s familiar?
Answer: A black cat

In witchcraft legends, what is the name of the large cooking pot witches use?
Answer: A cauldron

What vegetable were Jack-o’-lanterns originally carved from before pumpkins?
Answer: Turnips

Which famous vampire lives in Transylvania?
Answer: Count Dracula

What is a group of witches called?
Answer: A coven

In the story “Hansel and Gretel,” what did the witch use to lure the children?
Answer: A house made of candy (gingerbread)

What supernatural creature is said to transform during a full moon?
Answer: A werewolf

Which Halloween creature is traditionally repelled by silver bullets?
Answer: Werewolves

What color combination is most associated with Halloween?
Answer: Orange and black

Which ghost-warding item is said to protect homes from evil spirits when hung above the door?
Answer: A wreath of garlic (or just garlic)

What classic Halloween monster is created by stitching together body parts and brought to life with electricity?
Answer: Frankenstein’s monster

What famous witch movie features the Sanderson sisters?
Answer: Hocus Pocus

In folklore, what creature sits on your chest and causes nightmares or sleep paralysis?
Answer: A mara (or “nightmare demon” / “old hag”)

What is the name of the friendly ghost in the popular cartoon series?
Answer: Casper

What’s the name of the holiday in Mexico that honors deceased loved ones around the same time as Halloween?
Answer: Día de los Muertos (Day of the Dead)

Which spooky creature is known for wrapping itself in bandages?
Answer: A mummy

What is the traditional Halloween game where people try to bite floating fruit in water?
Answer: Apple bobbing

In mythology, what creature is half-man and half-goat, often associated with mischief?
Answer: A satyr or faun
